{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9a634b12-c0b9-46ce-a812-1428388fe736","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01NLjVq3Ue6ucCWMg3r9zaaP","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Creating runsettings migration"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01KZ8TnKp6gmVrL8XBTnAhHq","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-dc4b77799383446ab01843c6dd62736a/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <!-- Replaces <Property name=\"TestTimeout\" value=\"30000\" /> from .testsettings -->\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n    <!-- Replaces AssemblyResolution / DeploymentItem behaviour -->\n    <DeploymentEnabled>true</DeploymentEnabled>\n  </MSTest>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <!-- Replaces the CodeCoverage data collector from .testsettings -->\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n                     uri=\"datacollector://microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n                     assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.dll\">\n      </DataCollector>\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-dc4b77799383446ab01843c6dd62736a/local.runsettings."}],"interactionId":"7e0248b3-bd5b-4374-8ba8-1950a757b509","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a `.testsettings` file with:\n1. Assembly resolution / test deployment configuration\n2. A test timeout of 30000ms (30 seconds)\n3. A code coverage data collector\n\nIn MSTest v3, `.testsettings` files are no longer supported. The configuration needs to be migrated to a `.runsettings` file and/or MSTest attributes/properties in the `.csproj`.\n\nLet me explain the migration path:\n\n1. **Test timeout** → Use `[Timeout]` attribute on test methods, or configure it in `.runsettings` under `<MSTest><TestTimeout>`.\n\n\n2. **Code coverage data collector** → Configure in `.runsettings` under `<DataCollectionRunSettings>`.\n3. **Assembly resolution / deployment** → MSTest v3 handles deployment differently; the `<DeploymentItem>` attribute or `.runsettings` `<MSTest><DeploymentEnabled>` can be used.\n\nThe overall migration involves creating a `.runsettings` file and removing the `.testsettings` reference.","outputTokens":625,"requestId":"2417:9FE27:42D27E:47A33C:6A031072"},"id":"5398148e-a484-45da-8b5c-ced2bb7a4b68","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:35:26.369Z","parentId":"7610b566-aa27-4ebb-88e0-8e4685625828"}
