{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3d162a31-a825-4b2c-ac98-a1881c784512","content":"Here's a summary of the migration:\n\n**`.testsettings` is not supported in MSTest v3.** Replace it with a `.runsettings` file. I've created `local.runsettings` that maps each setting:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `<Property name=\"TestTimeout\" value=\"30000\" />` | `<MSTest><TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>` |\n| `<AssemblyResolution> / useLoadContext` | `<MSTest><DeploymentEnabled>true</DeploymentEnabled>` |\n| CodeCoverage `<DataCollector>` | `<DataCollectionRunSettings><DataCollectors>` (updated URI to v2.0) |\n\nThe `.csproj` now points to the `.runsettings` via `<RunSettingsFilePath>`, so `dotnet test` will use it automatically. You can also pass it explicitly:\n\n```\ndotnet test --settings local.runsettings\n```\n\nOnce verified, you can safely delete `local.testsettings`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7e0248b3-bd5b-4374-8ba8-1950a757b509","outputTokens":262,"requestId":"2416:A9EA2:42679D:47414D:6A03107F"},"id":"84d7875f-0067-4c0e-bb99-88376c1387d4","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:35:37.828Z","parentId":"f496bede-2559-435c-a758-39ab13c6387e"}
